"Hidalgo J., Masson V., Baklanov A., Pigeon G., Gimeno L.","Advances in urban climate modeling",2008,"Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences","1146",,,"354","374",,,10.1196/annals.1446.015,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-57249105479&partnerID=40&md5=4e6ee49c6d5a3b7c95ee70660ea60a53","Universidad de Vigo, Departamento de Física Aplicada, Facultad de Ciencias de Ourense, Ourense, Spain; Centre National de Recherches Meteorologiques/Groupe d'Etude de l'Atmosphere Meteorologique, Météo-France/CNRS, Toulouse, France; Danish Meteorological Institute, Research Department, Copenhagen, Denmark; Área de Física de la Tierra (Grupo FA09), Universidade de Vigo (Campus de Ourense), As Lagoas - 32004, Ourense, Spain","Hidalgo, J., Universidad de Vigo, Departamento de Física Aplicada, Facultad de Ciencias de Ourense, Ourense, Spain, Centre National de Recherches Meteorologiques/Groupe d'Etude de l'Atmosphere Meteorologique, Météo-France/CNRS, Toulouse, France, Área de Física de la Tierra (Grupo FA09), Universidade de Vigo (Campus de Ourense), As Lagoas - 32004, Ourense, Spain; Masson, V., Centre National de Recherches Meteorologiques/Groupe d'Etude de l'Atmosphere Meteorologique, Météo-France/CNRS, Toulouse, France; Baklanov, A., Danish Meteorological Institute, Research Department, Copenhagen, Denmark; Pigeon, G., Centre National de Recherches Meteorologiques/Groupe d'Etude de l'Atmosphere Meteorologique, Météo-France/CNRS, Toulouse, France; Gimeno, L., Universidad de Vigo, Departamento de Física Aplicada, Facultad de Ciencias de Ourense, Ourense, Spain","Cities interact with the atmosphere over a wide range of scales from the large-scale processes, which have a direct impact on global climate change, to smaller scales, ranging from the conurbation itself to individual buildings. The review presented in this paper analyzes some of the ways in which cities influence atmospheric thermodynamics and airborne pollutant transport. We present the main physical processes that characterize the urban local meteorology (the urban microclimate) and air pollution. We focus on small-scale impacts, including the urban heat island and its causes. The impact on the lower atmosphere over conurbations, air pollution in cities, and the effect on meteorological processes are discussed. An overview of the recent principal advances in urban climatology and air quality modeling in atmospheric numerical models is also presented. © 2008 New York Academy of Sciences.","Air pollution; Urban climate; Urban heat island; Urban meteorology; Urban modeling","air pollution; air quality; atmosphere; climate; conference paper; meteorology; microclimate; pollution transport; quantitative study; thermodynamics; urban area; Atmosphere; Cities; Climate; Models, Statistical; Urbanization",,,,,,"(1995) GURME - The WMO Gaw Urban Research Meteorology and Endvironmental Project, , http://www.cgrer.uiowa.edu/people/carmichael/GURME/GURME.html, GURME WMO. Project web-site; (2007) The Physical Science Basis., p. 996. , IPCC, Climate Change. Contribution of Working Group I to the Fourth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, Cambridge University Press. Cambridge, United Kingdom and New York, NY, USA, 2007, pp; Crutzen, P., New directions: The growing urban heat and pollution 'island' effect - Impact on chemistry and climate (2004) Atmos. Environ., 38, pp. 3539-3540; Molina, M.J., Molina, L.T., Megacties and atmospheric pollution (2004) J. Waste Manag. Assoc., 54, pp. 644-680. , &; Carmichael, G.R., Shan, H., Calori, G., (1999) The Effect of Aerosol on the Chemistry and Climate of Urban Environments, , Proc. of 15th Int. Congress of Biometeorology and Int. Conf. on Urban Climatology, Sydney, 8-12 November 1999; (2007) Mitigation., p. 852. , IPCC, Climate Change. Contribution of Working Group III to the Fourth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, B. Metz, O.R. Davidson, P.R. Bosch, R. Dave, L.A. Meyer, Eds.: 